o3 Answer:
Use the Quotient Rule for exponents:  

If a ≠ 0, then a^m / a^n = a^{m-n}.

a)  u^{24} / u^{3} = u^{24-3} = u^{21}

b)  9^{15} / 9^{5} = 9^{15-5} = 9^{10}

(You can leave 9^{10} in exponential form or evaluate it as 3 486 784 401.)

